                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d715">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/94: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-19T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 19, 1931—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. Reber’s No. 70, March 11, 3 p.m., and Department’s 66, March 12, 2 p.m.<note
                        n="41" xml:id="d715fn41">Latter not printed.</note> The Finance Corporation
                    states that no request for funds for sanitation for the use of Dr. Howells
                    and/or other medical officer designated by the International Committee has been
                    received from the Liberian Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
